U.S. Naval Academy STEM Center for Education and Outreach's Dr. Angela Moran, the "Mother of USNA STEM," recently retired after 27 years of teaching! 

Dr. Moran is passionate about helping people reach their full potential and she not only taught and mentored midshipmen but also created #STEM programs for youth in underserved communities. She taught them about the endless possibilities of the world around them and encouraged everyone to believe in themselves.

#USNASTEM #WomeninSTEM

node.text:
Last month, Dr. Samara Firebaugh, Associate Provost for Academic Affairs and Tim Disher, Director, International Programs traveled in Egypt to explore academic and cooperative engagement opportunities for students. 

In Alexandria, they were hosted by the Commander in Chief of the Navy, Admiral Khaled and the Superintendent, Egyptian Naval College, Rear Admiral Mahmoud. 

In Cairo, the USNA team was hosted at the American University of Cairo @auc_egypt (AUC). Discussions throughout the visits were encouraging for professional and academic activities for midshipmen with the Egyptian Naval College and rich academic and research opportunities for Arabic language majors and minors and #STEM majors at AUC.  The Egyptian Navy sends students for the four-year international student program and one recently graduated with the Class of 2021. 

These in-person visits enhance the goals of our @usdepartmentofdefense for improving foreign language proficiency, understanding of important regions around the globe and appreciating other points of view.  Additionally, expanding programs whereby our future leaders can interact at a formative stage in their professional development are investments that will provide important leadership skills.

node.text:
Sail on ⛵️

Last month, 1/C Olivia de Olazarra and 2/C Caden Scheiblauer were hand picked to represent the United States at the @cismmilsport world sailing championships hosted at the Spanish Naval Academy in Marin, Spain. 

Nine countries were represented including Denmark, France, Greece, Italy, Portugal,  Russia, Spain and Ukraine. 

CISM is an international sports organization whose mission is "Friendship through sport". 

The #USNA team finished 7th after four days of intense racing.  The friendships developed over the week will last a lifetime and contribute to better understanding amongst our allies.
